title: One COVID-19 fatality confirmed
body_lines: Health officials confirmed one COVID-19 death on Saturday and the country’s COVID-19 death toll currently stands at 16,505.
The COVID-19 death confirmed on Saturday was over 60 years. Of the total COVID-19 deaths, 76.28% are over 60 years, 22.4% are between 30 and 59 years, and 1.31% are below 30 years.
A total of 9,317 COVID-19 deaths confirmed to date are male and 7,188 are female. The COVID-19 death confirmed on Saturday was male.
